Package: uforemote
Title: 
  A remote client for function migration and execution in separate processes
Version: 0.1.0
Author:      Konrad Siek <siekkonr@fit.cvut.cz> 
Authors@R: c(person(given = "Colette", family = "Kerr", role = c("aut"),
                    email = "colette.m.y.kerr@gmail.com"),
             person(given = "Konrad",  family = "Siek", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                    email = "siekkonr@fit.cvut.cz"))
Maintainer: Konrad Siek <siekkonr@fit.cvut.cz>
Description:
  This is a package that listens for requests to execute code by other 
  processes. The code is transferred via a socket in the form of serialized 
  byte-code compiled functions. The client deserializes the function, executes 
  it, and passes back the result.
License: GPL-2 | GPL-3
SystemRequirements: Rust tool chain w/ cargo, libclang/llvm-config, userfaultfd
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
